3 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
4 Sec. 1. OFFICE OF NEW AMERICANS STUDY COMMITTEE; REPORT
5 (a) Creation. There is created the Office of New Americans Study
6 Committee to make recommendations for creating an independent Office of
7 New Americans.
8 (b) Membership. The Committee shall be composed of the following
9 members:
10 (1) the Director of the Vermont Refugee Office, who shall be Chair;
11 (2) one member, appointed by the Commissioner of Labor;
12 (3) one member, appointed by the Executive Director of the Office of
13 Racial Equity; and
14 (4) six members, appointed by the Governor, one who must be a New
15 American with lived experience, who shall include:
16 (A) one member, nominated by the Association of Africans Living in
17 Vermont;
18 (B) one member, nominated by the U.S. Committee for Refugees and
19 Immigrants;
20 (C) one member, nominated by the Vermont Afghan Alliance;
21 (D) one member, nominated by the Brattleboro Development Credit
22 Corporation;
