1 (E) one member, nominated by Migrant Justice; and
2 (F) one member, nominated by the Vermont State College System.
3 (c) Powers and duties. The Committee shall study and submit a written
4 report to the House Committees on Commerce and Economic Development
5 and on Government Operations and Military Affairs and the Senate
6 Committees on Economic Development, Housing and General Affairs and on
7 Government Operations concerning recommendations for creating an
8 independent Office of New Americans, including:
9 (1) a summary of the current demographic, economic, and public health
10 data regarding New Americans in the State and information regarding the
11 government services being utilized and underutilized by New Americans;
12 (2) a summary or survey of varying and successful approaches to
13 providing government services to New Americans in other states, with
14 particular focus on the topics of the role of education and training institutions,
15 professional licensing, housing, and support for employers and municipalities;
16 (3) in consultation with community-based organizations composed of or
17 serving New Americans, the Vermont Asylum Assistance Project, State
18 agencies and departments that provide services to New Americans, the
19 Secretary of State’s Office, municipal government leaders, educational
20 institutions, and business leaders, information on:
